comments.body:
(yes, I know SCEV might optimize out whatever I'm writing here, before the coros pass even, this example is just to illustrate)
```
Generator<int> test(int n, int x, int *p) {
  co_yield 0
  for (int i = 0; i != n; ++i) {
     // CoroSplit reloads `p` and `x` inside the loop
     // If we had C++ TBAA typing for `frame`, the load/store into `frame->p` and reload of `x` (load `&frame->x`)
     // are MayAlias, since they are both accessing type int.
     // but of course, the address of frame->x is never taken anywhere and p is necessarily non-aliasing with it.
    *p += x;
  }
}
```
Regarding the TBAA roots, yes, I am just making it always use the C++ one.

